review_blob: Not a bad scottish ale. Nicely done smooth finish but nothing over the top to give this a glowing recommendation. I will try this one again. I dont think my rating will change.
This was my most dissappointing beer of this Sampler Pack. Maybe I drank a bad bottle but this doesnt rate high for me. Rather bland and too bready for my palate. Disappointing.

Finished second to Yellow Kite as my favorite beer of this sampler pack. Very nice IPA but not at the top of my favorites. Something I really enjoyed was the blending of the bitter/grapefruit/malt/hop concoction. Again, this is a beer I would recommend others give a try.

Of the Sampler Pak I bought in Ft. Collins, this was my favorite beer. Classic Pilsner taste, clean and crisp, very drinkable. Started as well as it finished. I would stock this beer in my cellar. I enjoyed this one very much!!!

Huge billowy head lives up to the mug shot on the label. Very smooth, drinkable IPA. Very hoppy, grapefruit flavors in every sip. I am a IPA fan and this is definitely a well priced beer I will continue to consume. Nice amber color and finishes very nice. I like a little bitter kick at the end. This one wont dissappoint!!!
My neighbor gave a couple of bottles of this one to try. Hoppy, malty, citrusy and very tasty start to finish. I enjoyed this one very much and would stock it if it were available in colorado.

Very Nice Apa!!! I would drink more of this Longmont brewery. I wish I could have sampled their offerings at the Longmont Oktoberfest. Comparable to Sierra Nevada Pale ale in a can or bottle. Better than SN PA on tap. Malty, hoppy and nice finish. I definitely like colorado beers!!!

Woodsy first taste. Big Alaskan Brewery Fan. Hits the sides of my tongue with a burst of flavors. Coffee, Bread and chocolate hints make me like this beer and Colorado for my local liquor store to have it. I do taste a cough drop component but again faint. I will definitely stock this one in my cellar.

Light Amber color, nice frothy head. Head didnt last long. A little sweet to the taste buds. Not much of a finish. Could be a very good hot weather beer but unfortunately we have snow. Revisit this one again when spring arrives.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: I enjoyed this beer. I have had other Brown ales that were better. Roasted coffee taste and a nice finish. I would stock this.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Ive rated allot of Leinenkugel much higher than the rest of the ratebeerians. I wasnt particularly impressed with the Wheat. Its middle of the road. Not my favorite leinie.

A little more like Michelob Ultra than I expected. Smooth, drinkable but no flavor beginning, middle or end. I would just rate this as a nice hot weather beer. Nothing to run out and buy a case though.

I really enjoyed this beer. Found it on my recent trip to Corral Liquors in Granite City, IL. A hint of spice with a smooth middle and nice finish. I tried it because I hadnt rated a seasonal Schlafly before. Would stock this if I lived closer.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Found this beer at Corral Liquors in Granite City, Illinois while driving through. This beer for me is pretty bland. Not what I expected. Coffee taste and bitter finish. Will have to come back and re-rate this one.

Sierra Nevada Torpedo makes great beer. More bitter than hoppy and very drinkable. I enjoyed this beer very much. Finishes smoother and dryer than I expected. Great Beer, Great experience. If this were available at my Liquor store Id stock in my fridge.

Very hoppy first initial taste. Finishes very strong and bitter. Excellent flavors and blends. Its complex and very satisfying beer for anyone looking for a beer that doesnt disappoint. Best Schlafly Ive ever had.

Excellent Imperial Stout!!! Ive had more complex flavors but this is smooth and very drinkable. I would recommend this beer to any Imperial Stout lover!!! Ive yet to have a bad bottle of Samuel Adams. I think you will enjoy this as much as I did. Nice coffee/licorice blend and finishes like black glass. Cocoa head and rich flavor.
beer_name: Samuel Adams Imperial Series Imperial Stout

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: I thought it was very nice. Hot here in Georgia and it when down smooth. Are there better Ambers??? Sure but this is a good effort on the part of leinie. Nice malt flavor and sweetness to make a thirst quenching summer beer!!!
Very good Apa. Great flavor and a brew Im unfamiliar with in Georgia but I will consume more of in the future. Hoppy and malty with a nice finish. Another beer I would recommend.

My next door neighbor gave me a bottle of this to try. Very very enjoyable brew!!! Maltly and aromatic and bottom line tastes great!!! Full bodied with lots of gravity in every sip. ODell doesnt make an inferrior beer. I would definitely recommend this one to anyone who enjoys this style of ale.

beer_brewer_name: Leinenkugel Brewing Company (Tenth & Blake Beer Co.)
review_blob: Not exactly what I was expecting but it is a great hot weather beer for a 100+ degree day. A tea with lemon flavor, drinkable, and the leinie taste fans of this beer would expect. Surprised its for sale down here in Georgia but thats a good thing. Will drink it again.

Bought this after my move to Georgia. Didnt realize until after I had drank it that it was a AB product. Not the best wit Ive had but not the worst. Tasted like a michelob with spices. Didnt do much more for me than that. Using whats left to cook my brats with. Not much more you can say.
Had this one with my Neighbor. Awesome beer!!! Very good smooth, Finished very nicely would love to get more.
beer_name: Boulevard Smokestack Series - The Sixth Glass Quadrupel

review_blob: Thick dark black brown liquid with a deep medium brown thick head. Nose is chocolately and hints of a deep roasted malt. Flavor is a warming mix of roast coffe and dark chocolate. Bearutiful finish. Thick satiny body. A stunning beer. Let this one sit for 2 years before I popped it. Was well worth it!!!
Dark Red Coloring. Small Head. Very excellent Raspberry Taste...not overpowering. Sweet....and tart at the same time...very well balanced. Wonderful Fruit Beer!! Thank you JPDipso!!!

Hazy medium red w/ ok head. Aroma is big fruity cherry and floury wheat. Big juicy cherry up front, tart finish. Very active carbonation tingles the tongue and complements the cherry acidity nicely. Given to me courtesy of JPDipso.
Has a nice hoppy taste mixed with a decent malt taste. Pretty expensive (3 dollars a bottle) but well worth it. Will get more and stock this one. Excellent!!!

beer_brewer_name: Portland Brewing Company (Pyramid - North American Breweries)
review_blob: Was given this bottle in a trade with Indra. Sat refrigerated for a couple of years. Complex flavor. The body was quite full with smooth carbonation and a creamy texture. I enjoyed it.
Found this one At Gomers Lees Summit. Pours a light clear amber with a medium white head. I enjoyed it, not top of the line but a good beer.
Pours a crystal clear pale yellow with a large white head. Was a nice beer. Not as fond of the Lagers as I once was but tastes change.
Sat in my fridge for a solid year before I tried and I really enjoyed it. Hadnt been online much but my notes of this beer were very good and as all good things come to an end so did this one.
Crimson pour with a light tan head. This is backed by a light hop flavor and a mild bitterness. Bottle was given to me from my next door neighbor. Not bad.
Very light color with white head. Crisp sweet lager with a hint of corn perhaps.
Had this with my neighbor. Thought the rating was low because its a big 3 beer. Very tasty and wish it would be a regular in the Coors lineup. Smooth, drinkable and perhaps the best beer in the Line.

Had this one last night amazing beer. New Glarus is one of the Meccas of the MIcro beer world. Full body and very satisfying. Great beer and its a shame that distribution keeps it from escaping Wisconsin now.
beer_name: New Glarus Unplugged Bourbon Barrel Bock

review_blob: Excellent beer!!! Very Satisfying. Definitely a must try and one you should have on your wish list.
I forgot to rate this beer. One of the best wheats I have tasted. I had it while on vacation in fort myers, florida earlier this year. Definitely a must try.
Had this beer on my brithday at Kelsos Pizza in North Kansas City. Smooth drinkable beer. Very nice, Nice citrus flavor. Great beer.

Very good wheat. Clean, crisp refreshing especially on 100 degree days. Comparable to boulevard and a solid contender in this category. 4 very nice beers reviewed that deserve looking into the rest of the Offallon line.
Very smooth drinkable blonde. Im very impressed with the quality of Offallon beers. Ive had a few better in this category but this was very nice. Worth looking into.
My 2nd favorite of the four I tasted. Definite peach flavored wheat beer. Very Nice crisp, refreshing hot weather beer. Another great offallon beer.

Best beer of the 4 Ofallon beers Ive tried. smokey,roasty, chocolate in a very well balanced porter. One of the better Porters Ive had in a long time. A definite must have if you live in or are passing by the Midwest. Great beer.

I had intended on having another Stout for number 500 but I cant think of a better brand than New Glarus to annoint this milestone. This is definitely a sweet stout, very smooth, black glass liquid with big flavor and served up at its optimum temperature makes for gourmet slushing. Big sweet chocolate flavor no part of this beer overpowers but it lets you know its there. Great Beer to christen my 500th!!!
Sweet and tasty. Amber colored beer goes down smooth and is very satisfying. Maltly flavor put this one heads above most marzens I tasted. Not the best Ive had, but a solid effort.

Smuttynose Imperial Stout is a terrific beer!!! Chocolate, coffee, licorice, full bodied awesome drinking experience. Ive never had a bad Smutty. Big frothy head dark volcanic glass color. Excellent Imp. Stout!!!
beer_name: Smuttynose Big Beer Series: Imperial Stout

review_blob: Very nice IPA!!! Ive like some flying dog brews better but this was a very nice IPA. I enjoyed this beer very much and its now available in my region so thats a plus but its not a top tier IPA.
Bitter without much flavor after the first pop. Ive had better in this category. I would rate this as average.

Excellent APA. Nice grapefruit flavor mixed with strong hop/malt presense. Very enjoyable beer. It would be nice if it were available in this area. I believe this is my first Kentucky beer. I really enjoyed it.

Alpha Klaus is the best porter Ive had. Potent, coffee, licorice, grapefruit, huge head out of the bottle. Big Time Flavor with nice hop malt mix. Cant do better in the porter department than this.I have one rated higher and another equally rated. Tough to pick whos best.
beer_name: Three Floyds Alpha Klaus Christmas Porter

review_blob: Odells makes some of my favorite beers. There are a few breweries who never disappoint. Odells has been one of those for me.Nice head out of the bottle. Sweet, golden color, faint hop/malt tastes. Very refreshing beer. Very good beer.
